   {:e #blake3 "c28b031582938783fed5d7fb28e2abbfa83754910342fa8cccbdf7dcec1e89ae" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :session/s-1774195173; Session entity: :recon/trace-5e2a86f8bfade871; DEEP REVIEW SESSION 033: 6 strengths identified (EAV model, bilateral loop, harvest/seed, cotransactions, gradient routing, self-bootstrapping). 6 problems decomposed to axioms: P1 F(S) V-component dishonesty (V=0.04, should be ~0.5), P2 task overload (321 open, 83 likely done), P3 guidance footer noise (constant signal = no signal), P4 store loading O(n) startup (15-30s), P5 zombie spec markdown (deprecated but still richer than store), P6 witness system shallow depth (231 L1 witnesses are keyword matches, not proofs). 5 solutions proposed: (1) Test-to-witness pipeline, (2) Incremental store cache, (3) Interrupt-driven guidance, (4) Task stage-gating, (5) Spec datom enrichment. Critical path: Solution 2 then Solution 1. Estimated 9 hours total for all 5.; ACTIVE OBSERVER: The single most accretive addition is making braid an active epistemic agent. Continuous passive observation via filesystem watchers, git hooks, test runner adapters, MCP tool interception. Policy manifest defines what to watch and how to interpret. Auto-generates datoms through extractor pipeline and COTX routing. Agent never runs a braid command. The system is always observing, checking boundaries, computing gradients. The daemon (ADR-STORE-006) is not just performance but the active observers runtime. Eliminates ceremony permanently. Basin A wins by being autonomous, not just invisible.; SOLUTION-3 (Interrupt-Driven Guidance): Replace always-on footer with delta-triggered interrupts. Show footer only when F(S) changed or anomaly detected. OVERFITTING RISK: Low — the interrupt model is information-theoretic, not project-specific. Any store mutation that changes F(S) triggers it. VERDICT: Safe, but the specific anomaly detectors should be configurable, not hardcoded.; Session entity: :task/t-fda2952f; Session entity: :recon/trace-6f9d2d6483409d0e; Session entity: :task/t-c176a338; BRAID IS A COHERENCE SUBSTRATE, NOT A SOFTWARE TOOL. The plugin architecture is not an add-on but the structural consequence of C8 (substrate independence). If DDIS methodology must enter through plugins, then any methodology can. The protocol (detect divergence, classify, resolve to coherence) is universal. Applications: legal compliance, scientific research, product development, manufacturing quality. Each registers domain-specific plugins for claims, evidence, boundaries, and fitness components. The kernel provides the datom store, query engine, boundary registry, plugin framework, and harvest/seed lifecycle.; Session entity: :task/t-ca2af3c5; Session entity: :recon/trace-7376bf7c3e982152; Session entity: :recon/trace-d02718af7276b7fb; INSIGHT CHAIN 3/5 — DECLARATIVE POLICY MANIFEST: The epistemological policy (what counts as a claim, what counts as evidence, how coherence is measured, what boundaries matter) must be datoms in the store, not compiled Rust code. At braid init, a manifest is transacted: claim types, evidence types, boundary definitions with weights, anomaly detectors. The kernel reads the manifest and configures itself. Different domains get different manifests. The 7-component F(S) becomes one possible configuration, not the only one. Traces to: C3 (schema-as-data), C8 (substrate independence).; LLM-BOOTSTRAPPED EPISTEMOLOGY: braid init starts a conversation with the user about their domain. What are your claims? What counts as evidence? What boundaries matter? What would alarm you? The LLM generates a policy manifest from natural language and transacts it as genesis datoms. The conversation IS the first harvest. The system self-configures its epistemological policy from a dialogue about domain knowledge. This closes the entire loop: the observer defines the rules of its own knowledge game, and the substrate enforces them.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ed549dbb9995855e; Session entity: :recon/trace-09ae24af5f509d6f; SOLUTION-4 (Task Stage-Gating): Add :task/stage attribute to filter ready queue by project stage. OVERFITTING RISK: Low — stages are a generic project management concept. The 5-stage model (0-4) is from SEED.md but any project could define their own stages. VERDICT: Safe if stage values are not hardcoded to DDIS stages but stored as project-level configuration datoms.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ae997c8a1a10b8fc; Session entity: :recon/trace-b0033903ccf82a58; CRITICAL FEEDBACK: Risk of overfitting braid to its own bootstrap problem. Five solutions proposed in session 033 review may tether braid to Rust-specific tooling (Kani, cargo test JSON, clippy), our spec markdown format (Level 0-4 hierarchy), and our specific project conventions. The tool must remain universally applicable: any language, any spec format, any team methodology. SEED.md S4 says EAV is schema-on-read precisely to avoid hardcoding ontology. Solutions must use the extractor pattern (ADR-FOUNDATION-009): language-specific logic in extractors, universal logic in kernel.; Session entity: :recon/trace-1691669648b04abf; Kernel Methodology Agnosticism; SOLUTION-1 (Test-to-Witness Pipeline): Parse test runner output to auto-create L2 witnesses. OVERFITTING RISK: Proposed as cargo test JSON parser — this couples braid to Rust/cargo. CORRECTED DESIGN: Use extractor pattern (ADR-FOUNDATION-009). The kernel provides witness_from_test_result(spec_ref, pass/fail, test_hash, file) — language-agnostic. A Rust extractor parses cargo test JSON. A Python extractor could parse pytest. A Go extractor could parse go test. The kernel never sees cargo.; INSIGHT CHAIN 5/5 — ACTIVE OBSERVER: The most accretive addition is making braid an active epistemic agent. Continuous passive observation through policy-defined watchers: filesystem changes, git commits, test results, MCP tool calls, editor activity. The daemon (ADR-STORE-006) is the active observers runtime. Eliminates ceremony permanently. Basin A wins by being autonomous, not just invisible. The agent never runs a braid command. The system maintains coherence continuously. Traces to: ADR-STORE-006 (daemon), MCP-EXTRACT-1..5 (behavioral signals), INV-GUIDANCE-001 (continuous injection).; INSIGHT CHAIN 4/5 — LLM-BOOTSTRAPPED INITIALIZATION: braid init starts a conversation about the users domain. What are your claims? What counts as evidence? What boundaries matter? What would alarm you? The LLM generates a policy manifest from natural language and transacts it as genesis datoms. The conversation IS the first harvest. The system self-configures its epistemology from dialogue. The bootstrapping conversation is itself an instance of the protocol it configures. Traces to: SEED.md S10 (bootstrap principle), C7 (self-bootstrap).; SOLUTION-5 (Spec Datom Enrichment): Migrate Level 0-4 hierarchy from markdown to store. OVERFITTING RISK: HIGH. The Level 0-4 formalization (algebraic law, state invariant, implementation contract, proptest strategy) is DDIS-specific methodology. Not every project has algebraic foundations. A web app team's specs look completely different. CORRECTED DESIGN: The kernel should support arbitrary structured attributes on spec entities (:spec/section-* with free-form keys), not a hardcoded 4-level hierarchy. The DDIS Level 0-4 would be one convention, not the only one.; DEEPEST INSIGHT: DDIS is a formal epistemology. Braid is a runtime for formal epistemology. The datom is the minimum viable unit of shared belief. The append-only constraint is epistemic integrity. CRDT merge is intersubjectivity. The fitness function measures epistemic progress. The gradient computes optimal inquiry. The harvest/seed cycle enables cumulative knowledge. The 8-type divergence taxonomy is an epistemological taxonomy. The plugin system is the policy interface between domain-specific epistemological policies and the universal substrate. C8 preserves braids nature as a runtime for arbitrary epistemological policies.; Session entity: :recon/trace-548c5c5412e3bd00; Session entity: :task/t-0506cba8; Session entity: :recon/trace-79b3e09bdea44d5e; Session entity: :recon/trace-7a131b64cdc470c6; Session entity: :recon/trace-ff6019e37e815b9d; Session entity: :recon/trace-6b56b09c128bb96f; Session entity: :recon/trace-db081b0e65929cc6; INV-FOUNDATION-006 (proposed): Kernel Language Agnosticism. The braid kernel MUST NOT contain logic specific to any programming language, test framework, spec format, or project methodology. All domain-specific behavior enters through extractors (ADR-FOUNDATION-009) registered as datoms. Falsification: any kernel module that imports, parses, or assumes a specific language ecosystem (cargo, jest, go test, pytest) violates this invariant. The test: would this code make sense if braid managed a React project? If no, it belongs in an extractor, not the kernel.; Session entity: :recon/trace-864e09efcf0939c9; SOLUTION-2 (Incremental Store Cache): Delta-apply new transactions to cached store instead of full rebuild. OVERFITTING RISK: None — this is pure store internals. The datom store, transaction files, and cache are braid's own abstractions. No language or project coupling. VERDICT: Safe to implement as proposed.; INSIGHT CHAIN 1/5 — C8 SUBSTRATE INDEPENDENCE: The braid kernel must not contain logic specific to any programming language, test framework, or methodology including DDIS. All domain-specific behavior enters through plugins registered as datoms. Added as hard constraint C8 in CLAUDE.md alongside C1-C7. Traces to: SEED.md S4 (schema-on-read), ADR-FOUNDATION-009 (extractors-as-datoms).; Session entity: :task/t-ea458965; Session entity: :recon/trace-12f565c9324e328a; Session entity: :recon/trace-ded3fe1ea5ced0c4; Braid as Epistemology Runtime — substrate/application separation; Policy Manifest Completeness; Session entity: :recon/trace-5ca1a279b7f109d2; INSIGHT CHAIN 2/5 — FORMAL EPISTEMOLOGY: DDIS is not a specification standard. It is a formal epistemology. Braid is a runtime for formal epistemology. The datom is the minimum viable unit of shared belief. Append-only is epistemic integrity. CRDT merge is intersubjectivity. F(S) measures epistemic progress. The gradient computes optimal inquiry. Harvest/seed enables cumulative knowledge across mortal observers. The 8-type divergence taxonomy is an epistemological taxonomy universal across all domains. Traces to: SEED.md S1-S2.; SUBSTRATE vs APPLICATION separation insight: braid conflates universal substrate (datom store, query, boundaries, extractors) with DDIS-specific application (INV/ADR/NEG, 7-component fitness, witnesses, Level 0-4). The kernel hardcodes DDIS concepts in bilateral.rs, witness.rs, MaterializedViews. The fix: ensure DDIS dog-foods the same extensibility mechanisms external users would use. DDIS should be braids first customer, not its identity.; Declarative Policy Manifest as genesis datoms; Session entity: :task/t-f2b41d54; Session entity: :recon/trace-4e31d16a5c41d5fc" :op :assert}
